Hide the in-game dialogue window when Conversation is in DS mode, so the companion
(bottom-screen) dialogue UI is the sole conversation surface; show the native window
when Conversation is Vanilla.

Re-gated July 2026 from the global Hide UI flag (mHudEnabled) onto the per-element DS
flag companionDsConversation() (androidmain.cpp, pushed from Kotlin's
"game_ui_conversation" GameUiMode). DS -> suppress the native window; Vanilla -> show it.
updateVisible() runs at the end of pushGuiMode/popGuiMode, so the gate is applied the
moment the dialogue mode is entered — not only on a Hide UI toggle.

Unlike the HUD (mHud) and the tooltip layer (mToolTips), the dialogue window's
visibility is NOT driven by updateVisible() at all in vanilla — it is toggled by
GuiModeState::update(visible) on GM_Dialogue push/pop. We add the gate here, in
updateVisible() (called at the tail of pushGuiMode/popGuiMode), because this is the
single place window visibility overrides are applied.

Gate choice — getMode() == GM_Dialogue, NOT containsMode() and NOT isVisible():
  * isVisible() cannot restore the window: once we hide it, isVisible() is stuck
    false, so it could never become visible again when Conversation is set back to
    Vanilla — the window would stay gone for the rest of the conversation.
  * containsMode(GM_Dialogue) is too broad: GM_Dialogue stays on the mode stack
    while a service window (Barter/Spells/Travel/...) is pushed on top. Vanilla
    hides the dialogue window during barter (the pushed mode calls the previous
    mode's GuiModeState::update(false)); a containsMode gate would force it back
    visible behind/over the service window every updateVisible().
  * getMode() == GM_Dialogue is exactly the condition under which vanilla shows
    the dialogue window (dialogue is the topmost/active mode). When a service
    window is pushed, getMode() is no longer GM_Dialogue, so we leave the window
    alone and vanilla's own hide stands — no barter/service regression.

Hiding mid-conversation is safe: WindowBase::setVisible(false) calls onClose(),
but DialogueWindow::onClose() early-returns while containsMode(GM_Dialogue) is
true (see companion-dialogue-export.patch), so it neither clears mHistoryContents
nor emits COMPANION_DIALOGUE_CLOSED. setVisible(true) re-shows it (onOpen is a
base no-op for DialogueWindow), so switching Conversation back to Vanilla restores
the exact same open conversation.

This patch also declares the three Phase-1 companionDs*() bridges (used here and by
companion-hide-container-on-hideui.patch / companion-hide-barter-on-hideui.patch,
which are applied after this one in the chain and share this translation unit).

--- a/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp
+++ b/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp
@@ -640,6 +640,15 @@
         mConsole->updateSelectedObjectPtr(currentPtr, newPtr);
